The only thing that could make a substantial improvement to the situation would be a coherent European agenda from the Commission and the Council.
Global trade is important and of great benefit in enabling developing countries to escape from the vicious cycle of poverty; much is to be gained by a good combination of aid and trade, and the process of combining the two must not be allowed to stand in the way of these countriesâ development; it is in this way that we will be able to achieve the Millennium Goals.
What I am calling for is a coherent European agenda; the new development cooperation instrument can provide it with a framework.
